918	  Let \(A\) be a ring, \(M, N\) two \(A\)-modules with \(N\) Noetherian (in
919	  particular, finite over a Noetherian ring \(A\)), and \(\varphi : M \to N\) an
920	  injective \(A\)-linear map. Then \(M\) is a finite \(A\)-module. This is the
921	  submodule-finiteness step in \cref{lem:graded_polyQuot_finite_of_le_numerator}.
922	\end{lemma}
